The ONNX `Softmax` op does not convert one-to-one to `relay.nn.softmax` because older ONNX Softmax ops have [very strange spec](https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/main/docs/Changelog.md#Softmax-11): In particular, it cannot support doing softmax on the `C` dim in NCHW input, for example.

Our converter manually decomposes softmax into simpler ops. This prevents benefiting from future improvement in our softmax kernel implementation (fusing max, exp, sum etc into one kernel as in https://triton-lang.org/getting-started/tutorials/02-fused-softmax.html). So for cases that can convert to `relay.nn.softmax` directly, we should use it.

